verses.text_plain: O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased; O turn thyself to us again.
verses.verse_html:
1O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased; O turn thyself to us again. ▼
▼ Michtam: or, A golden Psalm
 , ▼
▼ scattered: Heb. broken

tokens.text: O turn thyself to us again

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Michtam: or, A golden Psalm

verses.text_plain: Thou hast made the earth to tremble; thou hast broken it: heal the breaches thereof; for it shaketh.
verses.verse_html: 2Thou hast made the earth to tremble; thou hast broken it: heal the breaches thereof; for it shaketh.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast shewed thy people hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment.
verses.verse_html: 3Thou hast shewed thy people hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment.

tokens.text: thou hast made us to drink

verses.text_plain: Thou hast given a banner to them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 4Thou hast given a banner to them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.

tokens.text: thee, that it may be displayed

verses.text_plain: That thy beloved may be delivered; save with thy right hand, and hear me.
verses.verse_html: 5That thy beloved may be delivered; save with thy right hand, and hear me.

verses.text_plain: God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.
verses.verse_html: 6God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.

verses.text_plain: Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;
verses.verse_html: 7Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;

verses.text_plain: Moab is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe: Philistia, triumph thou because of me.
verses.verse_html:
8Moab is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe: Philistia, triumph thou because of me. ▼
▼ triumph…: or, triumph thou over me :(by an irony)

footnotes.body_text: ▼ triumph…: or, triumph thou over me :(by an irony)
footnotes.body_html: ▼ triumph…: or, triumph thou over me :(by an irony)

verses.text_plain: Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
verses.verse_html:
9Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom? ▼
▼ strong…: Heb. city of strength?

footnotes.body_html: ▼ strong…: Heb. city of strength?

verses.text_plain: Wilt not thou, O God, which hadst cast us off? and thou, O God, which didst not go out with our armies?
verses.verse_html: 10Wilt not thou, O God, which hadst cast us off? and thou, O God, which didst not go out with our armies?

verses.text_plain: Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
verses.verse_html:
11Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man. ▼
▼ help of man: Heb. salvation, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ help of man: Heb. salvation, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ help of man: Heb. salvation, etc

verses.text_plain: Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
verses.verse_html: 12Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
